ly 0.1 per giga-parsec\ncube. If the surrounding submm sources in these fields are at the same\nredshifts as the central objects, then the total star-formation rates of these\ncandidate protoclusters reach 10,000 solar masses per year, making them much\nmore active at these redshifts than what has been seen so far in both\nsimulations and observations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 6 Oct 2020 17:42:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-10-13"}
